description: A modular machine learning framework for building, training, and evaluating regression models on multivariate time-series data. Includes preprocessing utilities, sliding-window generation, custom model pipelines, feature selection, and performance visualization.

Comprehensive machine learning framework for genomic analysis and predictive modeling. This repository showcases advanced classification and clustering techniques using XGBoost, CatBoost, LightGBM, and RandomForest to identify genetic disorders. Includes association rule mining with Apriori and unsupervised geographical clustering via KMeans.
Demo web app that demonstrates how different types of machine learning detection models (object, segmentation, keypoint) work seamlessly within a same framework.
Code for AdaNUMA: A Machine Learning-Guided Adaptive NUMA Scheduling Framework

AI-powered Digital Forensic Investigation Framework for detecting anomalies in marine navigation systems using Python, Machine Learning, and evidence hashing, with integrated Blockchain support for secure, tamper-proof evidence and information storage.

An advanced cryptocurrency trading bot and predictive analysis framework exploring the potential of automated "passive income" through machine learning. Features implementation of XGBoost, Random Forest, Transformer, and Reinforcement Learning for signal generation

An organized collection of Python projects categorized by domain and complexity.   Beginner Projects: Basic scripts, simple games, utilities  Intermediate Projects: Web apps, data analysis, automation  Advanced Projects: Machine learning, complex systems, APIs  Tools & Libraries: Reusable code, packages, frameworks

ytopt: machine-learning-based autotuning and hyperparameter optimization framework using Bayesian Optimization

E2E (Easy to Ensemble) is a novel R package designed to provide a comprehensive and flexible framework for ensemble machine learning, specifically tailored for medical applications like diagnosis and prognosis.

This is the synthetic dataset used for the paper "A Hybrid Machine Learning Framework for highly imbalanced data: Predicting Hurricane Losses in Parametric Insurance"  by Yangchongyi Men, Roberto Guidotti, Javier Cuartas, Angel A. Juan, Guillermo Franco, Patricia Carracedo and Laura Lemke-Verderame.

A fast, distributed, high performance gradient boosting (GBT, GBDT, GBRT, GBM or MART) framework based on decision tree algorithms, used for ranking, classification and many other machine learning tasks.

Developed a Fake Currency Detection System utilizing continual learning and incremental training techniques within deep learning frameworks. Demonstrated proficiency in deploying adaptable machine learning models for real-time currency verification.

An explainable machine learning framework to predict post-synthesis timing slack (WNS) directly from RTL Verilog designs. Uses static RTL feature extraction, Random Forest regression, and SHAP explainability to provide early, interpretable timing insights.

MPMR-IMCP is a two-stage AI framework. It first uses a Vision Transformer to identify mucin expression from H&E whole slide images, then applies machine learning to integrate image features and clinical data for predicting intestinal metaplasia cancer risk.

brpc is an Industrial-grade RPC framework using C++ Language, which is often used in high performance system such as Search, Storage, Machine learning, Advertisement, Recommendation etc. "brpc" means "better RPC".

This repository implements an end-to-end machine learning framework for mental health data analysis, including preprocessing, regression, classification, and clustering. Random Forest models achieve superior predictive performance, while PCA and K-Means reveal hidden patterns to support data-driven mental health insights.

A curated portfolio of AI, Machine Learning, and Automation projects showcasing expertise in deep learning, NLP, web scraping, and data visualization. Includes work on recommendation systems, face embeddings, financial forecasting, and applied AI solutions built with Python, FastAPI, Django, and modern ML frameworks.
A comprehensive machine learning framework for fault diagnosis in CMOS integrated circuits, developed as part of a directed study under Prof. Duncan M. Walker at Texas A&M University.

Collection of projects applying data science and quantitative finance techniques  from portfolio optimization and CAPM estimation to machine learning and ESG event analysis  to explore real-world financial datasets and decision-making frameworks.

This repo contains machine learning and deep learning models for various problems, using frameworks like scikit-learn, TensorFlow, and PyTorch. It includes ML algorithms, neural networks, and notebooks demonstrating data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation.
This project presents a hybrid anomaly detection framework combining Machine Learning and Deep Learning models to identify cloud-based cyber threats.

Web App for the Metal Input Line Entry System (MILES)  a comprehensive framework for describing surface properties using a standardized line notation format. MILES strings can be converted to numerical representations suitable for machine learning models in materials science applications.

Es un framework avanzado para la ejecucin de pipelines de datos que combina automatizacin, escalabilidad y flexibilidad. Diseado para simplificar la gestin de flujos de trabajo complejos de datos, desde ETL tradicionales hasta pipelines de Machine Learning.

ML-Pipe-Deploy is a comprehensive, open-source framework that simplifies and standardizes the deployment of complete machine learning pipelinesfrom data processing and model training to serving and monitoring. It transforms scattered ML scripts into production-ready, scalable, and maintainable systems with minimal configuration.
gCoSRNA, a generalizable machine learning framework for predicting coaxial stacking in RNA junctions using only sequence and secondary structure information.
MORSE (Model Optimization tools for Remote Sensing Data Analysis) is a Python-based framework for optimising machine learning models for multi-modal remote sensing data.

The solution operationalizes advanced machine learning pipelinesspanning LightGBM, XGBoost, CatBoost, Random Forests, and Neural Networks

This repository contains the complete, end-to-end reproducible pipeline developed for the manuscript:  Integrated Machine Learning and CRISPR Scoring Framework for Prioritizing Therapeutic gRNAs Targeting TCF7L2 in Type 2 Diabetes.

Petastorm library enables single machine or distributed training and evaluation of deep learning models from datasets in Apache Parquet format. It supports ML frameworks such as Tensorflow, Pytorch, and PySpark and can be used from pure Python code.

It integrates machine learning models with a user-friendly interface to support farmers and service providers in making informed agricultural decisions..

The work proposes a comparative machine learning framework for predicting salaries in global AI job market using diverse job-related features. Several regression models, including Linear Regression, Ridge, Lasso, ElasticNet, Random Forest and Gradient Boosting are evaluated using an 80/20 traintest split with 10-fold cross-validation.

This project presents an end-to-end machine learning framework for predicting NFL Draft outcomes using collegiate performance data utilizing over 17,000 NCAA players collected from the CollegeFootballData API.

This project presents a practical approach to improving retail inventory accuracy using data-driven forecasting. By combining statistical models, modern machine-learning techniques, and reinforcement learning, the study builds a structured framework capable of predicting demand, planning reorder cycles, and reducing supply-chain inefficiencies.

Matplotlib  Python Data Visualization Library  Matplotlib is a powerful and widely used Python library for data visualization. It provides a flexible framework to create static, animated, and interactive plots, making it an essential tool for data analysis, scientific computing, and machine learning projects

Temporal machine learning framework for early sepsis risk prediction based on multivariate ICU time-series data, leveraging a stacked (LSTM) architecture. Beyond retrospective evaluation, the model was deployed within a lightweight mobile application, enabling real-time inference, and visualization of short-term risk trajectories.

A full-stack heart disease prediction web app built using Django REST Framework, React, and Machine Learning. It uses Logistic Regression to predict heart disease based on medical inputs. The app features a responsive UI, REST APIs, and real-time predictions.

This repository contains a complete, end-to-end research framework for understanding how monetary liquidity regimes shape equity valuations, factor returns, and market dynamics. The project combines macro-finance theory, econometric modeling, and modern machine learning methods to build a structural interpretation of liquidity-driven markets.
